        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>Container arrived too late; Vehicle missed
Assign to a new vehicle.
Keep Container in Bay</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2145267497">
        <posattr x="1062.000000"
                 y="-158.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>1 TD and 1 to many CRs are created at this activity.
ID counters for TDs are incremented; ID counter
for CRs is increased based on the number of created
CRs.</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2145267828">
        <posattr x="-252.000000"
                 y="-42.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>In this model, timestamps of events are atomic.
Execution delays/waiting times between two activities
are sampled before the execution of the second activity.
For example, here &quot;CreateTDDelay&quot; is applied before
&quot;Create Transport Document&quot;.</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2145268617">
        <posattr x="283.000000"
                 y="378.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>At the beginning of the simulation,
logs (.csv files) are created according to
the tables of OCEL2.0.</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2145268977">
        <posattr x="-321.000000"
                 y="355.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>Adapt this number to increase or decrease the
size of the output log.</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2145270346">
        <posattr x="2417.000000"
                 y="42.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>TDs are &quot;in transit&quot; as soon as all containers 
have been moved to the terminal.</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2145271043">
        <posattr x="5275.000000"
                 y="-1302.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>These places control the timed business logic according
to which containers are moved within the terminal.</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2145273204">
        <posattr x="6072.000000"
                 y="-294.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>Vehicles are &quot;created&quot; twice a week, setting the departure time
to four weeks in the future.</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2145892778">
        <posattr x="5865.000000"
                 y="-630.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>Containers that missed the Vehicle are kept at the Loading Bay
near the Loading Ramp
until the next is available. They are not returned to the Stock</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2146182305">
        <posattr x="3390.000000"
                 y="-84.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>Could also add &quot;Weightbridge&quot; as Location, 
though its not much different from any other case, so we leave it out</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2146274058">
        <posattr x="3498.000000"
                 y="-1150.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>Location Based Task Alloc, for Forklifts
use last location for cost
e.g. 
Terminal -&gt; Terminal = 100
Storage -&gt; Terminal = 500
Loading Bay -&gt; Terminal = 1000</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2146657381">
        <posattr x="3497.000000"
                 y="-1260.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>Forklift remains at current location until reassigned
only then it moves to the new location. 
does not return to the depot</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2146944985">
        <posattr x="5554.000000"
                 y="-588.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>only FL enters Loading Bay,
Container is already there</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2147288446">
        <posattr x="2856.000000"
                 y="-815.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>Trucks randomly enter the North or South Terminal</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID-2147407364">
        <posattr x="7350.000000"
                 y="273.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>might slow simulation down</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID-2147294969">
        <posattr x="7235.000000"
                 y="42.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>Containers never formally leave the Loading Bay
Thus there might be more Enter- than Leave-Events</text>
      </Aux>
      <Aux id="ID2147018877">
        <posattr x="2058.000000"
                 y="42.000000"/>
        <fillattr colour="White"
                  pattern=""
                  filled="false"/>
        <lineattr colour="Black"
                  thick="1"
                  type="Solid"/>
        <textattr colour="Black"
                  bold="false"/>
        <label/>
        <text>This throws an error if there are less than 
8 vehicles available when booking</text>
      </Aux>
    </page>
